article.headline: Austin Peay 73, E. Illinois 57
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Drake Reed had 14 points, Caleb Brown scored 12 and Austin Peay beat Eastern Illinois 73-57 Monday night. Todd Babington added 9 points and 4 rebounds for the Governors (10-6, 6-0 Ohio Valley Conference), who are tied with Southeast Missouri State for the best record in the conference. Julio Anthony led the Panthers (2-13, 1-6) with 17 points, and Jake Byrne added 9 points for Eastern Illinois. Derek Wright's 7 points and 7 assists also lifted Austin Peay. Austin Peay burst out to a 38-24 halftime lead, and kept the cushion with 48 percent shooting from the floor. The Governors also drew plenty of fouls, and converted 20-of-22 free throws. Tyler Laser and Gino Myers-Kyles scored 9 points apiece for Eastern Illinois, which was 8-for-11 shooting free throws.
